article.headline: Cent. Michigan 70, Wright St. 68
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. -- Robbie Harman hit a 3-pointer with 1.4 seconds to play in overtime, as Central Michigan defeated Wright State 70-68 on Saturday. Harman scored nine points, including a 3-pointer with seven seconds left in regulation to force the extra frame. The Chippewas (2-2) trailed the Raiders (0-2) 59-49 with 4:07 to play, but five points from Jeremy Allen sparked a 12-2 run to close regulation. Allen finished with 22 points to lead Central Michigan whie Jacolby Hardiman had 10 points and 10 rebounds. Wright State was led by Cory Cooperwood, who had 16 points and 11 rebounds.
